                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the north base of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Varadarāja Perumāḷ shrine in the Chandramauḷīśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Vikramachōḷa. Year 8: 1125-26 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription records the gift of 12 sheep for a <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamp to the Āḻvār at Tiruvakkarai in Māttūr-nāḍu by Śēṭṭan (Jyēshṭhan) Tiruvāṟai, a shepherd of Gaṅgaikoṇḍaśōḻapuram in Naḍuviṟ-kūṟu in Śōḻa-maṇḍalam. The sheep were made over to the care of Kulaṅgiḻavan Āttraiyan Tirunāḍuḍaiyāṉ, a lease-holder of the temple.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
